\begin_layout Title
Welcome to soundLab!
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Spring 2026 Weekend Session
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Thank you so much for joining us for our March 21-22 soundLab session.
 This document will help get you started,
 so you know where to go and what's happening.
 If you have any questions,
 please do not hesitate to contact us at millerp3@duq.edu or mcmasterm@duq.edu.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Locations,
 Entrances,
 Times
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Dates
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

and
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

times Saturday,
 21 March 2026 from 9:00am to 4:00pm and Sunday,
 22 March from noon to 4:00p.m.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Location Physics Labs,
 2nd Floor,
 Fischer Hall.
 You can find a campus map at:
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "https://www.duq.edu/campus-map.php"
target "https://www.duq.edu/campus-map.php"
literal "false"

\end_inset


\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

Once you are inside Fischer Hall,
 you can take an elevator to the 2nd floor.
 The best place to enter the building is probably from the Fischer Skywalk which goes over Forbes Avenue.
 You can enter the Skywalk from McAnulty Drive.
 Students can be dropped off at the Student Union and walk down the hill with the Gumberg Library on the right.
 There will be signage in Fischer Hall directing you to the labs.
 We may also use space in the Mary Pappert School of Music,
 but our main location is Fischer Hall.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Lunch We will provide free lunch to paid registrants on Saturday,
 21 March.
 This will be at Duquesne's Towers cafeteria.
 We will all walk over across campus together as a group and eat lunch in the faculty/staff dining room.
 Towers is a buffet-style 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

all you can eat
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 situation.
 There are many options here for those with special dietary needs,
 but if you are unsure please contact one of us and we will do our very best to accommodate you.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
Equipment If you have a laptop computer,
 please bring it.
 If you do not,
 that is perfectly fine:
 we will provide one for you to use during the workshop.
 Although these school laptops can be used at Duquesne,
 we kindly ask that they not be taken off campus.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset

We will give each registered student a goodie bag with all the hardware they require.
 This does not need to be returned.
 If necessary,
 additional hardware and electronics components are available.
\end_layout

